--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Yes, the game has changed. It's easier to level now but, in the end, I think it's much harder to reach the top-end. Tell me what is easier, for a true newbie:<br>
<br>
A) Reach level 50 in pre-kunark days or<br>
B) Reach level 65 +120 AAs today.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I'd say about the same. Pre kunark people usually needed 50+ days of played to reach level 50, when you can do that now in 5-6 days untwinked and not powerleveled. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
For those of you who didn't start playing until after Kunark was released, let me tell you what went on.<br>
<br>
There were only two high-level (level 40-50 players)  EXP  zones in the game: Lower Guk and Sol B.  I played on E'ci and on any given night, there were 70+ people in these two zones.   You could literally walk from the zoneline to deep inside the two dungeons without fear of getting attacked.   Because there were 10+ full groups in various spots of the dungeons, it was a footrace between the pullers to get a mob when it popped.  If you didn't pull it within seconds of it popping, another group would get it.   <br>
<br>
The reason it took so long for everyone to level back then wasn't because the game was too hard, it was because there weren't enough places for level 40-50s to hunt.   It was boring as hell camping in Lower Guk and Sol B because inevitably you had extended periods of downtime waiting for a mob to pop so you could fight. <br>
<br>
I stopped playing my bard on E'ci when Velious was the latest content.  I was level 54 with over 70 days played.   I started playing my magician here on FV in August 2002.  I'm level 63 now with 30 AAs.  My /played time is around 30 days.   The main reason I leveled so much faster with the magician is because every night I play, I can hunt in areas where there is an endless supply of mobs to pull.  I didn't have that luxury with the bard.   <br>
